	"description": "Those who work with me know that I’m always obsessing about performance. Words\nlike: critical rendering path, bundle size and frames-per-second are a common\nthing around the office. But it’s all for a good reason.\n\nPerformance should be a first class citizen in software engineering.\n\nHaving a strong performance culture in your team can ensure that you mitigate —\nahead of time — any risks associated with bad performance.\n\nBut why is it so important? And what are those risks?\n\nWhy performance matt",
